Just south of the Brandenburg Gate is Berlin’s Holocaust Memorial, with its two thousand, seven hundred and eleven gray concrete slabs, or stelae. The installation is a living experiment in montage, a Kuleshov effect of the juxtaposition of image and text. The text in question is the title of the memorial: in German, Denkmal für die Ermordeten Juden Europas—a Memorial to the Murdered Jews of Europe. •

#unlimitedberlin #visit_berlin #berlino #wonderlustberlin #berlingram #visualscollective #theimaged #artofvisuals #ig_mood #bravogreatphoto #featremeofh #capturedconcepts #roamtheplanet #lifeofadventure

In the city of Berlin, on September 24th, our journey towards memory begins with a first major theme: the persecution of the Jews. The emotions and curiosity push us to know the story of a minority that has been crushed. The anguish and sadness helped us to better understand the injustices they suffered. Our images represent the two possibilities these people had: death and hope.
